    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-10-28T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-10-28T07:00:00-05:00" n="129"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d129">
                <head>129. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Embassy in Austria</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d129fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 764.00/10–2856. Confidential.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <hi rend="italic">
                            <placeName>Vienna</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                                when="1956-10-28T13:00:00+01:00">October 28, 1956—1 p.m.</date>
                        </hi>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>916. We are encountering among our Austrian friends a strong tendency to blame
                    the U.S. for the present predicament of the Hungarian patriots. Reference is
                    frequently made to <gloss target="#t_RFE1">RFE</gloss> and our balloon
                    operations as having incited the Hungarians to action and our failure to do
                    anything effective for them now that they have risen against their Communist
                    oppressors. When asked what we could do they have nothing to suggest.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_TLE1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Thompson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
